est German Court's decision on Bonn and Paris treaties:\n\nAlthough the West German Constitutional Court rejected on 7 March the government's petition for an immediate ruling on the Bonn and Paris treaties, the Bundestag is expected to ratify them by the end of March. Bundesrat approval, however, has now become much more unpredictable and will probably not be forthcoming until summer, when the federal election campaign gets under way.\n\nIn any event, the opposition Social Democratic Party will almost certainly resubmit its case to the court should both houses of parliament approve the treaties in the next two months.\n\nShould the court then declare the treaties incompatible with the constitution, a decision which is now somewhat more likely, a governing coalition of all major parties might be formed following the elections. After some delay this coalition would likely \"re-ratify\" the treaties by amending the constitution", "token_count": 150, "token_end_0based": 149, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "western europe 4 comment on west german court's decision on bonn and paris treaties although the west german constitutional court rejected on 7 march the government's petition for an immediate ruling on the bonn and paris treaties the bundestag is expected to ratify them by the end of march bundesrat approval however has now become much more unpredictable and will probably not be forthcoming until summer when the federal election campaign gets under way in any event the opposition social democratic party will almost certainly resubmit its case to the court should both houses of parliament approve the treaties in the next two months should the court then declare the treaties incompatible with the constitution a decision which is now somewhat more likely a governing coalition of all major parties might be formed following the elections after some delay this coalition would likely re-ratify the treaties by amending the constitution", "unred_source_page": 5}
